<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-03-06T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-03-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.E/190: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-06T10:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 6,
                                        1923—10 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 12:42
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>10. With reference to previous correspondence on this subject, President
                            Leguía told me yesterday that to his great regret Peru would be unable,
                            in the present circumstances, to attend the conference at Santiago.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>